			"title": "Prompt Line Pick — usage",
			"properties": {},
			"widgets_values": [
				"Put one item per line. The **seed + node ID** determines which line is picked — `sha256(seed:nodeId) % lineCount`.\n\nKey feature: **each instance picks independently even with the same seed**, because the node ID acts as a channel discriminator. No need to manage different seeds per list.\n\nTip: connect the seed input to your KSampler seed for reproducible prompt/image pairs."
			],
			"color": "#232",
			"bgcolor": "#353"
		},
		{
			"id": 4,
			"type": "MarkdownNote",
			"pos": [480, 800],
			"size": [280, 360],
			"flags": {},
			"order": 6,
			"mode": 0,
			"inputs": [],
			"outputs": [],
			"title": "← Outputs",
			"properties": {},
			"widgets_values": [
				"| Output | Description |\n| ------:| -----------:|\n|**STRING**|the literal string of the selection|\n|**COMBO**|the selection, formatted for common third party prompt selectors (see examples →)|\n|**prompt_list**|accumulated pick stack (LIST type) — for chaining between pickers or with *easy promptList*; convert to text with *Something To String (KJ Nodes)*|\n|**prompt_strings**|same picks as a STRING list — for sending to other nodes; convert to text with *String List to String (Impact Pack)*|\n|**seed**|connect to other nodes seed inputs, to share the same seed (enable **uncorrelate** to pick **different lines** even if nodes use the same seed and have the same number of entries)|"
			],
			"color": "#232",
			"bgcolor": "#353"
		},
